        "client_msg_id": "b3b1d16e-dfe2-40bb-9c14-7b93f5441e6d",
        "text": "That's one reason why simulation has been such a success in scientific research, the other one being the possibility to study larger and more complex systems. But especially for more complex systems, visualization is what makes the simulations intellegible.\n\nUnfortunately, this also creates a \"what I see is truth\" attitude towards simulation that leads to uncritical acceptance of whatever \"the computer\" tells us. Wrong maths simulated looks just as convincing as correct maths simulated.",
